{%- capture tbp_disclaimer_html -%}<p>The information provided here is for educational and informational purposes only and should not be taken as veterinary advice. While our recipes are developed with guidance from qualified pet nutritionists and formulated to meet or exceed AAFCO standards, we are not licensed veterinarians or veterinary nutritionists.</p>
<p>Every pet is unique. Nutritional needs may vary depending on breed, age, activity level, health conditions, and other factors. We strongly recommend consulting your veterinarian before making significant dietary changes, especially if your pet has pre-existing medical conditions or special nutritional requirements.</p>
<p>All product descriptions, sourcing details, and preparation methods reflect our best knowledge and current practices. While we are committed to transparency and quality, our information is not a substitute for professional veterinary care.</p>{%- endcapture -%}
{%- capture tbp_overview_html -%}<p>At The Bon Pet, our mission is simple: to nourish pets with food that's as wholesome as it is delicious.</p>
<h3>We achieve this by</h3>
<ul><li>Using only fresh, human-grade, unprocessed ingredients</li><li>Deriving essential vitamins and minerals naturally from whole foods rather than synthetic supplements whenever possible</li><li>Carefully formulating every recipe with PhD-level pet nutritionists to ensure it meets or exceeds AAFCO standards for complete and balanced meals</li></ul>
<p>Every recipe we craft reflects our belief that pets deserve the same care, transparency, and respect we give to the food we eat ourselves.</p>{%- endcapture -%}
{%- capture tbp_sourcing_html -%}<h3>Chicken 🐔</h3>
<p>Our chicken is sourced from trusted farms in Malaysia, where chickens are typically blast frozen shortly after processing ("FZ local"). This quicker farm-to-freeze timeline helps retain juiciness and texture compared to many imported frozen chickens.</p>
<h3>Beef 🐄</h3>
<p>We source our beef from Brazil, which offers the best balance of quality and affordability. While beef from New Zealand and Australia is often considered premium, it is 3-5 times more expensive. Using only NZ/AUS beef would significantly increase prices for our customers. After internal testing, we found Brazilian beef provides a comparable texture and nutritional profile, allowing us to keep meals both accessible and high-quality.</p>
<h3>Kangaroo 🦘</h3>
<p>Our kangaroo is wild-caught from Australia, where it is naturally lean, rich in protein, and free from added hormones or antibiotics. As a novel protein, kangaroo is an excellent option for pets with sensitivities or allergies to more common meats.</p>{%- endcapture -%}
{%- capture tbp_cooking_html -%}<p>We gently cook all meals at 80°C, striking the perfect balance between safety, nutrition, and taste.</p>
<ul><li>Food Safety: At this temperature, harmful pathogens are eliminated while preserving the natural integrity of the ingredients.</li><li>Moisture Retention: Lower than boiling, 80°C reduces water loss, ensuring a juicier, more palatable meal.</li><li>Tenderness: At 60-85°C, collagen slowly breaks down into gelatin, creating a tender texture while locking in nutrients.</li></ul>
<p>This careful process ensures every bite is safe, nourishing, and delicious for your pet.</p>{%- endcapture -%}
{%- capture tbp_giving_html -%}<p>At The Bon Pet, we believe every pet deserves love, dignity, and a full belly  -  even those without a home.</p>
<p>That's why we partner with Wildflower Studio and LUNI (Love Uniting Neighbourhoods and Individuals), two inspiring Singapore-based initiatives dedicated to animal welfare and community care.</p>
<h3>Through these collaborations, we</h3>
<ul><li>Donate wholesome meals to rescued and fostered animals in need</li><li>Support adoption journeys by providing nutritious starter packs to new pet parents</li><li>Raise awareness about responsible pet ownership and animal welfare in our community</li></ul>
<p>When you choose The Bon Pet, you're not just nourishing your own pet  -  you're helping us extend that care to animals who need it most. 🐾</p>{%- endcapture -%}
